race.comment: SWAG (1) has been on the doorstep of a maiden victory hitting the top-four in six of seven starts to date and this is not an overly strong affair. Must be respected out of the Freedman barn and looks the one they all have to run down. The well-related HIGHGROVE ROSE (12) (half to G2 winner Not An Option) returned in good order with a close-up second here and looks ready for the extra furlong now. Likely improver second-up and has bright prospects. ENFORCEABLE (3) has placed three of four overall and only needs some luck from the wide draw to feature in the finish. DEVINE SQUIRE (2) has hit the frame in both career outings and may earn some minor money again. CARAMELFUDGESUNDAE (15) presents some value and is next in line from the inside marble.
